  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Normally, block creation is limited only by the block gas limit, not by the data size.\r\nHowever, the RLPx protocol for sending and receiving created blocks has a 24bit (16MB) data size limit.\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/devp2p/blob/master/rlpx.md#message-encoding\r\n\r\nThus, if Parity creates a huge block over 16MB,\r\nIt seems that there is a problem that it has the latest block but cannot send, and stops synchronization.\r\nhttps://github.com/paritytech/parity-ethereum/issues/11334\r\n\r\nDoes Geth have this problem?\r\nIf not, how do you avoid it?\r\n\r\nAlso, if you have an EIP that mentions this issue, could you tell me?\r\n\r\nThank you.",
